The paper deals with memory management in concurrent data structures and algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Operating Systems (cs.OS), Programming Languages (cs.PL), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). However, given the focus on memory reclamation, which is a key issue in concurrent data structures, cs.DS is the most likely category. The other categories are also relevant because they deal with issues related to concurrency and parallelism.
